aether.pro_tips.line.aether.moa_egg_incu: Moam Eggs can be incubated into baby Moams with the Incubator.
aether.pro_tips.line.aether.moa_nature_s: Baby Moams will stay put when right clicking them with a Nature Staff.
gui.aether.moa_skins.text.donate: Donate to the project to get Moam Skins!
gui.aether.moa_skins.title: Moam Skins
lore.block.aether.incubator: Used to incubate Moams. You use Ambrosium Torches for the fuel. The process can take quite some time, but it is worth the wait once your Moam of choice hatches!
lore.item.aether.aechor_petal: The petal of an Aechor Plant; they have a sweet aroma to them. These are a Moam's favorite food and can be used to feed baby Moams.
lore.item.aether.black_moa_egg: An egg laid by a Black Moam. Hatching this provides a Black Moam with 8 mid-air jumps, the best and most rare one!
lore.item.aether.blue_moa_egg: An egg laid by a Blue Moam. Hatching this provides a Blue Moam with 3 mid-air jumps. The most common Moam.
lore.item.aether.nature_staff: A staff that can allow for commanding tamed Moams. It can allow them to sit on the ground.
lore.item.aether.white_moa_egg: An egg laid by a White Moam. Hatching this provides a White Moam with 4 mid-air jumps. This Moam is decently rare.
